95. Write a Java program to create an array (length # 0) of string values. The elements will contain "0", "1", "2" â€¦ through ... n-1.

<OWN METHOD>
import java.lang.*;
import java.util.Arrays;
public class w3 {
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
       int n = 5;
       String[] arr = new String[n]; //Create a string array, n set the size
        
       for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            arr[i] = String.valueOf(i); //convert all int i to str, store in array
        }
        System.out.println("New Array: "+Arrays.toString(arr));//Print out the array in string form

    }
}

>>
New Array: [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]



<SAMPLE SOLUTION>
import java.util.*; 
import java.io.*; 
 public class Exercise95 {
 public static void main(String[] args)
 {
    int n= 5;
	String[] arr_string = new String[n];
	
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        arr_string[i] = String.valueOf(i);                                  
	 System.out.println("New Array: "+Arrays.toString(arr_string)); 
	 }
}
